	a specified year has.

@{b}   INPUTS@{ub}
	month - The month from which you want to get the number of days.
	year  - The year in which the month is.

@{b}   RESULT@{ub}
	days - The number of days the month uses, or 0 if you use
	    an incorrect month.

@{b}   EXAMPLE@{ub}
	unsigned short days;
	...
	days = date_JulianMonthDays(1,1994);
	printf("Days of January 1994 : %hu\n",days);
	...

@{b}   NOTES@{ub}
	It is better only to use this function for years from 8 to 09.1582!

@{b}   BUGS@{ub}
	No known bugs.

@{b}   SEE ALSO@{ub}
	@{"JulianLeapYear()" Link "JulianLeapYear()"},@{"GregorianMonthDays()" Link "GregorianMonthDays()"},@{"HeisMonthDays()" Link "HeisMonthDays()"}

